 There are two places a SKILL.md can live:
 
+## NO-ASSUMPTION Rule
+
+> Required for all skill execution. Prevents weak models from fabricating missing data.
+
+If information is missing:
+- do NOT infer
+- do NOT fabricate
+- STOP and report missing data with exact field name and source
+
+## Allowed Actions (Tool Boundary)
+
+> Required. Defines what the model MAY and MUST NOT do when executing this skill.
+
+The model MAY:
+- read files
+- edit approved files
+- run approved commands
+- call documented tool APIs
+
+The model MUST NOT:
+- delete unrelated files
+- modify secrets, tokens, credentials, or config containing auth
+- change architecture or system-level settings
+- run destructive actions (rm -rf, DROP, DELETE without verification)
+- use tools not listed in this skill's ## When to Use section
+
+## DONE Condition
+
+> Required. Prevents models from reporting PASS before workflow is actually complete.
+
+The task is DONE only if ALL of:
+- workflow completed (every numbered step executed)
+- verification passed (checks in ## Verification Checklist all checked)
+- required output exists (file, report, or confirmed state)
+- final report generated (status, files changed, exact sections added)
+
 1. **User-local:** `~/.hermes/skills/<maybe-category>/<name>/SKILL.md` — personal, not shared. Created via `skill_manage(action='create')`.
 2. **In-repo (this skill is about this case):** `/home/bb/hermes-agent/skills/<category>/<name>/SKILL.md` — committed, shipped with the package. Use `write_file` + `git add`. `skill_manage(action='create')` does NOT target this tree.
 
